			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Lad Tobin</strong></span> lives in New Hampshire and teaches at Boston College. He is the author of <em>Reading Student Writing: Confessions, Meditations, and Rants</em> and <em>Writing Relationships: What Really Happens in the Composition Class</em> (both Boynton/Cook). He is completing a memoir about his return, in midlife, to rock-music festivals, random acts of rebellion, and other teenage obsessions.</p><a href="/contributors/lad-tobin" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
